  "response": "```dockerfile
# Stage 1: Build Frontend
FROM node:20-slim AS frontend-builder
WORKDIR /app/frontend
COPY frontend/package*.json ./
RUN npm ci
COPY frontend/ ./
RUN npm run build

# Stage 2: Build Backend Dependencies
FROM python:3.12-slim AS backend-builder
WORKDIR /app
RUN apt-get update && \
    apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends gcc build-essential libpq-dev unixodbc-dev && \
    rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
RUN pip install --no-cache-dir poetry
RUN poetry config virtualenvs.in-project true
COPY pyproject.toml poetry.lock* ./
RUN poetry install --only main --no-root --no-interaction --no-ansi

# Stage 3: Runtime Image
FROM python:3.12-slim

LABEL maintainer="infrastructure@example.com" \
      description="Production image for Python Analytics Platform (inspired by Apache Superset / Redash)"

# Install runtime system packages (and curl for HEALTHCHECK)
RUN apt-get update && \
    apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
    libpq-dev \
    unixodbc-dev \
    curl \
    && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*

# Create non-root user 'superset' with UID 1000
RUN groupadd -g 1000 superset && \
    useradd -u 1000 -g superset -s /bin/bash -m superset

WORKDIR /app

# Copy python virtualenv from backend builder
COPY --from=backend-builder --chown=superset:superset /app/.venv /app/.venv
ENV PATH="/app/.venv/bin:$PATH"

# Copy frontend static assets from frontend builder
COPY --from=frontend-builder --chown=superset:superset /app/frontend/dist /app/static

# Copy remaining backend source code
COPY --chown=superset:superset . /app

# Switch to non-root user
USER superset

# Expose application port
EXPOSE 8088

# Healthcheck
HEALTHCHECK --interval=30s --timeout=10s --start-period=5s --retries=3 \
  CMD curl -f http://localhost:8088/health || exit 1

# Start command
CMD ["gunicorn", "-w", "4", "-b", "0.0.0.0:8088", "app:create_app()"]
